{
  "stem": "7739.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "The rest they used to march to the gas chambers, gas them, and burn them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And sometimes they used-- the transports used to arrive at a greater capacity than the gas-- than the gas chambers and the ovens were used to handle.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "So they had a big pit, looked like-- like a swimming pool.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "It used to burn day and night.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "They used to throw the children and the sick people in there alive.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And this-- you get used to it because you expect that you're going to be next, and you didn't give it another thought.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "There was this Sonderkommando whose job it was to herd the people into the gas chambers and then pull them out after they'd been gassed to feed the-- feed the [INAUDIBLE] the crematoria.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And a father of a friend of mine who I befriended in Birkenau-- nobody is supposed to know that this man had a son there.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "This wasn't a good thing to-- to-- to let any of the-- the administration know that you are related to anybody because they used you sometimes for these purposes.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they used to come in for the Russians.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They-- they were quartered in a-- in a camp.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had two barracks zoned apart from the-- from our camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Nobody could go in or out except for this Sonderkommando except this Sonderkommando sometimes slept in the gas chambers, and they did this purposely.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Any time they wanted to do away with them, [INAUDIBLE] they just dropped the gas in there, and the next day, they picked a new Sonderkommandos.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So very few of the-- very, very few people survived.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So they used to come and get the Russians to our-- to our camp.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
